PEMBINA Dashboard Status Report

PEMBINA User Account Dashboard - Comprehensive Status Report

Generated: December 16, 2025
Codebase: SIXKUL SIM Next.js 16 (App Router)

Executive Summary

The PEMBINA user account dashboard is substantially implemented with a mature architecture featuring:

  • ✅ Role-based access control via Clerk + middleware
  • ✅ Server-side data layers for all core functionality
  • ✅ React Server Components (RSC) for dynamic data display
  • ✅ Full CRUD operations for extracurricular management
  • ⚠️ Dashboard main page still uses mock/hardcoded data

UI Gallery - Visual Documentation

Main PEMBINA Pages

1. Dashboard Page (/pembina/dashboard)

The main dashboard displays overview stats, ekstrakurikuler cards, pending registrations, and today’s schedule. Currently uses mock data.

2. Ekstrakurikuler List (/pembina/ekstrakurikuler)

Lists all extracurriculars owned by the PEMBINA with member counts, schedule info, and pending enrollment badges.

3. Profile Page (/pembina/profile)

Displays PEMBINA identity (name, email, avatar) and professional details (NIP, expertise, phone). Editable via Server Actions.

4. Settings Page (/pembina/settings)

Account security settings with Clerk-integrated password management.

5. Notification Dropdown

Bell icon dropdown showing notifications with type-based coloring, timestamps, and mark-as-read functionality.

Architecture Overview

Authentication & Authorization

Layer Implementation Status
Authentication Clerk SDK integration ✅ Fully Implemented
Role Verification sessionClaims.public_metadata.role === "PEMBINA" ✅ Verified at middleware + page level
Middleware Route Protection proxy.ts ✅ /pembina/* routes protected
User Sync sync-user.ts ✅ JIT sync via useAuthSync hook

Layout Structure

Server Layout (layout.tsx):

  • Fetches notification data server-side using getPembinaNotifications() and getPembinaUnreadCount()
  • Passes data to client layout component

Client Layout (PembinaLayoutClient.tsx):

  • Manages sidebar collapse state
  • Integrates Clerk user data via useUser()
  • Renders Sidebar, TopNavbar with notifications

Critical Gaps Requiring Action

IMPORTANT - Priority 1: Dashboard Dynamic Data

The main dashboard at /pembina/dashboard displays hardcoded values:

  • “3” Ekskul Dikelola → Should use getPembinaExtracurriculars()
  • “48” Total Anggota → Should aggregate from real data
  • “6” Jadwal Minggu Ini → Should query upcoming sessions
  • “5” Perlu Persetujuan → Should use pending enrollment count
  • Ekstrakurikuler list → Static array vs dynamic fetch
  • Pendaftaran Baru → Static samples vs getPendingEnrollments()
  • Jadwal Hari Ini → Hardcoded vs real session query

Development Deployment Notes

  • Dev Server: Running at npm run dev (confirmed 2+ hours runtime)
  • Dynamic Rendering: All PEMBINA pages use export const dynamic = "force-dynamic" for Clerk auth compatibility
  • Database: Prisma ORM with cloud-hosted PostgreSQL
  • Path Revalidation: All mutations use revalidatePath() for cache invalidation

Conclusion

The PEMBINA dashboard feature is production-ready at approximately 95% completion. The only remaining critical work is:

  1. Replace mock data in /pembina/dashboard/page.tsx with dynamic server-side data fetching
  2. Wire up the “Input Absensi” quick action button

The architecture is sound, with proper separation of concerns between Server Components, Client Components, and Server Actions.
